# Allowlist build context: exclude everything, then re-include only the Go
# workspace inputs the Dockerfile compiles from. Keeps the context minimal so a
# new artifact (dump, binary, coverage) can't silently bloat the image or bust
# the layer cache. Keep in sync with the COPY lines in Dockerfile.
*

# Go workspace + the four modules (server is the binary; it needs proto via a
# replace directive, and go.work pins client/example too).
!go.work
!go.work.sum
!proto
!client
!server
!example

# Test files are never compiled into the binary (go build ignores *_test.go) —
# drop them to shrink the context.
**/*_test.go
